Chords is a responsive web app supporting user authentication.
Users can view and send song lyrics, guitar chords and tabs.

***This site is under heavy development!***

Requires
---------
python3
django (tested with version 1.8 only)
django-registration-redux
django-password-validation
django-recaptcha
django-bootstrap-form
django-compressor
django-appconf

Uses
-----
html5
jquery
bootstrap

Get started
------------
Make migrations:
`python3 manage.py makemigrations chords`
`python3 manage.py migrate`

Populate some test data (optional):
`python3 scripts/populate_chords.py`

Create a superuser for the admin site (optional):
`python3 manage.py createsuperuser`

Run the development server:
`python3 manage.py runserver`

You can now visit the site on http://localhost:8000.

Optionally you may also start a debugging mail server:
`python3 scripts/run_mailserver.sh`

That's required for user registrations and other stuff.
